                  Recomp 


Recomp is designed to help you to compress files on your epu device
or recompress them by another library.

Syntax:  Recomp source [all]

source - can be file or directory
         if source is directory Recomp needs largere stack than it's usual !!!
         - Recomp does not check the stack size and so it may cause guru !!!
all - also all subdirs will be (re)compressed

Example:

  You have file dh1:Data compressed by epu1 
  Now you want to have the file compressed  by NUKE (because it's faster).
    
    - install epu to dh1: with LOAD SAVE lib NUKE  settings.
    - type: Recomp dh1:Data

 
